PP_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT tells the compiler to emit a warning if a function's return value is not used by the caller.
Place this attribute at the very beginning of a function definition. For example, write
PP_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT int foo();
or
PP_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT int foo() { return 42; }

